{
  "title": "About Rcnoutliner Plugin",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "c7e4a913f2b8d046",
      "text": "The Rcnoutliner plugin embeds a hierarchical outliner directly in the wiki page. Nodes can be created, edited, indented, and reordered inline without leaving the wiki. Press Enter to add a sibling, Tab to indent, Shift-Tab to outdent, and F2 or double-click to edit."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "9f2b6e7a3d1c8054",
      "text": "Create an item using the factory. Click **MORE ↗** to open the full MORE Outliner in a popup window for advanced editing, Hoist, and export to Markdown, HTML, or FedWiki ghost page. Outline content is autosaved to the wiki via the sofi-proxy."
    },
    {
      "type": "rcnoutliner",
      "id": "5a3d8c1f4e9b7062",
      "text": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "1e6f9a4b2c7d3085",
      "text": "Developed by Marc Pierson with Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Anthropic) for the ReLocalize Creativity Network. Source: [[https://github.com/marpie1/wiki-plugin-rcnoutliner]]. Published on npm as wiki-plugin-rcnoutliner."
    }
  ],
